The paper discusses the role of data management in achieving causal algorithmic fairness, which involves addressing discrimination in machine learning systems. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including database systems (cs.DB) for managing and processing large datasets, machine learning (cs.LG) for developing algorithms that can learn from data, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for building intelligent systems that can reason about causality, cryptography (cs.CR) for ensuring the security and privacy of sensitive data, and social and information networks (cs.SI) for studying the impact of algorithms on social dynamics.
